      <tr>
        <td colspan="2"><div align="center"><span class="style12">ATTITUDE AND CAREER SUCCESS</span></div></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td colspan="2"><p align="left" class="style3">In the work environment, as in your personal life, it is your attitude that makes the difference . Building and maintaining healthy relationships among supervisors and co-workers is the key to success in any organization. Nothing contributes more to this process than a positive attitude. </p>
          <p align="left" class="style3">When positive, you transmit friendly signals. Customers, co-workers and supervisors are more open to you. Your attitude is expressed before you say a word. It shows in the way you look, stand, walk and talk. If you are cheerful and upbeat, your attitude acts like a magnet. You not only attract others, but they are more friendly toward you because they sense in advance that you already like them. </p>
          <p align="left" class="style3">Some individuals downgrade the importance of building and maintaining good human relations. So much emphasis is placed on the technical skills that they ignore the human issues. As a result, they have difficulty understanding why others often lack enthusiasm for their work although it is <strong><em>technically</em></strong> correct. One of the top reasons managers fail is that they cannot get their employees to do what they need them to do. Is this because they don't know how, don't want to do it or are not able to do it? Or is it because the employee takes on the attitude of &quot;Why should I?&quot; or &quot;What's in it for me?&quot; Where does this attitude come from? Wouldn't you like your employees to do exactly as you asked? Do you have the attitude that promotes that kind of dedication and respect from your staff? How would you feel if your staff was willing to do anything you asked of them quickly and with a smile. Earn the respect and dedication of your employees and you may not even have to ask. You can do this by having a good, strong, positive attitude of a teamplayer who wants to develop a winning team. </p>
          <p align="left" class="style3">Along with good work skills, career success depends on the quality of working relationships. An important first step is the development of a good attitude. If you don't look for the best in fellow workers, you are less apt to find it. As a result, you will not become the kind of manager Shari's wants you to be. Your personal productivity may remain high, but you will not be contributing as much as you could to the productivity of the organization.</p>
        <p align="left" class="style3">The well known saying that &quot;no man is an island&quot; is true. We all need other people. This is especially true in the workplace. Those who build a strong network of supporters create their own attitude reinforcement program. How great is it that you are surrounded by people to help keep you in a good mood? It is especially important in this business. You deal with guest and employee attitudes every shift you work. Often it is possible to turn a day that starts off poorly into one that is bright, simply because a fellow employee is in a good mood. Attitudes are truly infectious. </p></td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    <table width="640">
      <tr>
        <td width="114"><span class="style3 style7"><img src="../../../images/man_thinking.gif" width="68" height="118"></span></td>
        <td width="514"><div align="center"><span class="style3 style7">THOUGHTS TO PONDER </span></div></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td colspan="2"><ul class="style7">
          <li class="style3">
            <div align="left">Career success depends both on good work skills and human relations competencies. Building good human relationships must begin with a positive attitude. </div>
          </li>
          <li class="style3">
            <div align="left">Those who understand the importance of good human relationships, and are willing to initiate repairs when necessary, have a career advantage. </div>
          </li>
          <li class="style3">
            <div align="left">When a person is successful building and maintaining positive working relationships, a human support system is created that helps keep that person's attitude postive.</div>
          </li>
        </ul></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td colspan="2">&nbsp;</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td colspan="2"><div align="center"><span class="style12">Other Keys to Success Your Attitude Activates</span></div></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td colspan="2"><p align="left" class="style3"><img src="../../../images/key.gif" width="44" height="41">Confidence: Can you be confident and persuasive if you are not optimistic? I don't believe so. The confident person believes in his or her abilities and strides forward with the expectation of success. Your staff and supervisors can see and feel that confidence. Negativity breeds doubt and hesitancy. Confidence builds success. <br>
              <img src="../../../images/key.gif" width="34" height="35">Persisitence: You have to have a positive attitude to believe you will succeed and keep trying. How many times did you get back on that bike before you were able to stay on it? Giving up just leads to failure. <br>
              <img src="../../../images/key.gif" width="34" height="35">Resiliency: If you are a positive person you will only temporarily be frustrated with a circumstance or situation. You focus on correcting the situation, learning from it and you bounce back and try again.<br>
              <img src="../../../images/key.gif" width="34" height="35">Courage: Believe you can and move forward with courage. Set the example for your staff. Change is always going to occur. Your staff feeds off of your attitude. If you grasp hold of change and run with it your staff is more likely to embrace the change. <br>
              <img src="../../../images/key.gif" width="34" height="35">Enthusisasm and Energy: A good positive attitude helps build enthusiasm and energy. Customers can sense that enthusisam and energy. Of course you can over do enthusiasm and energy so be careful. Direct the over enthusiastic or energetic personality so as not to offend anyone. <br>
              <img src="../../../images/key.gif" width="34" height="35">Health: The cells of your body actually come alive when you are positive. A negative attitude can make a person physically ill and not want to come to work. It is amazing what the human brain can do. <br>
              <img src="../../../images/key.gif" width="34" height="35">Encouraging others: You have faith in the ability of others and they pick up on that. Your staff can sense that you have faith in their abilities or that you sincerely want them to do well. Having that confidence alone will help to improve staff attitudes as well as their performance. <br>
              <img src="../../../images/key.gif" width="34" height="35">Gratitude: When your outlook is negative you tend to focus your attention on what is wrong with everything . As you become more positive you start to see the good in people, in life, in yourself. You start to voice your gratitude and that alone will help improve another's attitude. <br>
              <img src="../../../images/key.gif" width="34" height="35">Perspective: This is a logical progression from your increasing feelings of gratitude. You appreciate the many positives in your life and recognize that they far outweigh any problems or temporary inconveniences such as an employee calling in sick. You don't let it tear you down or upset you because you realize it actually is a very minute problem when you focus on the big picture. <br>
              <img src="../../../images/key.gif" width="34" height="35">Approachability: It is much easier to approach a person with a smile on their face than one who has a frown. A smile is a sign of warmth and optimism where a frown just says &quot;stay away from me I am not in a very good mood.&quot; Your staff needs to know that you are always approachable and willing to listen. You may have to schedule a more convenient time but you are always willing to listen. Be there for your staff, mentally and physically. This can become draining if you do not have a strong positive attitude. <br>
              <img src="../../../images/key.gif" width="34" height="35">Spiritual growth: When you're filled with positive thoughts and feelings, you begin to appreciate yourself and others more. You begin to sense that there's a purpose behind everything and that you are a part of a bigger plan. You also trust your intuition and realize that you're receiving guidance on your journey. </p>
          <p align="left" class="style3">I think you would agree that this is a pretty impressive list of characteristics. And the way to access all of them is to build a more positive attitude. Never forget, however that your attitude is a choice you make everyday. The qulaity of your life and the impact you make in the world depends on that choice. Your Attitude is Everything!!!! </p>
        <p align="left" class="style3">&nbsp;</p></td>
      </tr>
